TC/{Time Constructible}/{A function \NNfunc{T} is \textit{time constructible} if $T\left(n\right)\geq n$ and there is a Turing machine $M$ that computes $x\mapsto\left\lfloor T\left(x\right)\right\rfloor$ in time $T\left(n\right)$.},
SC/{Space Constructible}/{A function \NNfunc{S} is \textit{space constructible} if there is a Turing machine $M$ that computes $S\left(\left|x\right|\right)$ in \bigoh{S\left(\left|x\right|\right)} space given $x$ as input.},
ILC/{Implicitly Logspace Computable}/{A function \ssfunc{f} is \textit{implicitly logspace computable}, if $f$ is polynomially bounded and the languages $L_f=\left\{\left\langle x,i\right\rangle |f\left(x\right)_i=1\right\}$ and $L_f'=\left\{\left\langle x,i\right\rangle|i\leq \left|f\left(x\right)\right|\right\}$ are in \cc{L}.}
